{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968/events","html_url":"https://github.com/doccano/doccano/issues/1968","id":1349827622,"node_id":"I_kwDOB-j9wM5QdLwm","number":1968,"title":"Have you thought of enabling WAL mode for SQLite?","user":{"login":"dylanjcastillo","id":7218756,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcyMTg3NTY=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7218756?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo","html_url":"https://github.com/dylanjcastillo","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dylanjcastillo/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":927327721,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw5MjczMjc3MjE=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"Improvement on existing feature"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2022-08-24T18:00:15Z","updated_at":"2022-11-19T09:20:59Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Have you thought of enabling SQLite's [Write-Ahead Logging](https://sqlite.org/wal.html)?\r\n\r\nThis allows simultaneous writes and reading, which would improve the performance when using SQLite with no real downside.\r\n\r\nI've done this in other Django projects using the `connection_created` signal (see example below). I'd be happy to make this change and open a pull request, if you'd like.\r\n\r\n```\r\n@receiver(connection_created)\r\ndef setup_sqlite(connection, **kwargs):\r\n    if connection.vendor != \"sqlite\":\r\n        return\r\n\r\n    with connection.cursor() as cursor:\r\n        cursor.execute(\"pragma journal_mode = WAL;\")\r\n        cursor.execute(\"pragma synchronous = normal;\")\r\n        cursor.execute(\"pragma temp_store = memory;\")\r\n        cursor.execute(\"pragma mmap_size = 256000000;\")\r\n```","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/doccano/doccano/issues/1968/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}